<%= faq_schema([
  { question: "How much topsoil do I need for a 1000 square foot lawn?", answer: "To top-dress a 1,000 square foot lawn with a 0.5 inch layer of topsoil, you need about 41 cubic feet, which is 1.5 cubic yards. For a deeper 2 inch fill over the same area, plan on roughly 6.2 cubic yards. Topsoil is heavy — 1 cubic yard weighs about 2,000 pounds, so a 2 yard order is close to 2 tons and almost always needs delivery rather than hauling in a pickup." },
  { question: "How many 40 lb bags of topsoil in a cubic yard?", answer: "A 40 lb bag of standard topsoil is about 0.5 cubic feet, and there are 27 cubic feet in a cubic yard, so you need 54 bags to equal one cubic yard. Expect to pay around 5 to 8 dollars per bag, versus 25 to 45 dollars per cubic yard in bulk. Above 1 cubic yard, bulk topsoil is dramatically cheaper even after delivery fees." },
  { question: "What is the difference between topsoil, garden soil, and compost?", answer: "Topsoil is the top 6 to 12 inches of natural mineral soil, screened and sold as a bulk fill product. Garden soil is topsoil that has been amended with compost and fertilizer for planting. Compost is fully decomposed organic matter — it is not a fill product. Use topsoil to raise grades, level lawns, and fill planters; use garden soil directly for planting; and use compost as a 1 to 2 inch amendment mixed into existing soil." },
  { question: "How much does a cubic yard of topsoil weigh?", answer: "Screened topsoil averages 2,000 pounds per cubic yard when dry, and 2,200 to 2,500 pounds per cubic yard when wet. A standard half-ton pickup can safely carry about half a cubic yard in a single trip; a full ton truck can handle one yard. For anything over 1 yard, pay the delivery fee — overloading a pickup is hard on the suspension and dangerous." },
  { question: "Can I use topsoil in raised beds?", answer: "Topsoil alone is too dense for raised beds; it compacts quickly and drains poorly. A good raised bed mix is roughly 60 percent topsoil, 30 percent compost, and 10 percent coarse aeration material like perlite or coarse bark. For that mix, use a raised bed soil calculator to split the volume three ways before ordering." }
]) %>

